description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and enthusiastic person to support the running of the Access Teams in North Somerset based at Long Fox Unit, Weston-super-Mare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a team that provides comprehensive administrative service to the clinical team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have excellent interpersonal skills, experience of typing letters, a good telephone manner, WP/IT skills and the ability to work both on your own and as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, you should have relevant office experience, a sound knowledge of Microsoft Word processing and a working knowledge of database systems. Audio typing would also be desirable, although not essential as training would be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working in a similar role and an awareness of mental health conditions would be desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal discussion please phone Carrie Bryant on 01934 523712&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carrie BryantJob tiBusiness Co-ordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address carrie.bryant@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01934 523712&lt;/p&gt;
